# Cascading Issue Chains (STORY-010 → STORY-014 → STORY-015)

Beyond flat Root Issue grouping, CivicChain models **directed causal relationships** between
individual issues — a blocked drain causes road flooding causes garbage accumulation causes
standing water causes a mosquito/dengue risk.

## How detection works (AI-driven — STORY-014)

Detection is **AI-driven**, not a static lookup table. When a new Issue is created, the system
gathers nearby open issues (within **500m** and **14 days**) as candidates and asks Gemini
(`src/lib/ai/detect-cascade.ts`, `detectCascadeWithAI`) to reason about whether the new issue
is a downstream *effect* of one of them, returning the single most likely upstream cause (or
null) plus a one-sentence `reasoning` and an internal `confidence`.

> **History:** STORY-010 originally shipped a static `src/lib/causal-graph.ts` category graph
> (a hand-listed `CAUSAL_EDGES` table of upstream→downstream category pairs). STORY-014
> **deleted that file** and replaced it with the Gemini call, because real civic chains are
> longer and more varied than any fixed table can enumerate. **Do not reintroduce
> `causal-graph.ts`, `CAUSAL_EDGES`, or `detectCascadeLink`.**

**Fallback (graceful degradation):** if the Gemini call fails (no key, network error, bad
JSON), a minimal pure-function rule fires — the closest open issue of the **same category**
within 500m and 14 days, or null. This is a safety net only, never the primary logic.

Detection runs best-effort inside the new-issue path — a failure never blocks report
submission.

## Provenance & reversibility (STORY-015)

Every link records **why** and **how** it was made:
- `reason` — the AI's one-sentence causal explanation (or the fallback rule's note).
- `source` — `"ai"` when Gemini detected it, `"rule"` when the same-category fallback fired.

The **LOCAL_BODY_HEAD** can undo a wrong link via `removeCascadeLinkAction` ("Not related"),
which deletes the `IssueChainLink` and clears `chainRootIssueId` on the downstream issue —
humans stay in control of AI suggestions, consistent with the platform's accountability rule.

## Schema

```prisma
model IssueChainLink {
  id                String   @id @default(cuid())
  upstreamIssueId   String
  downstreamIssueId String
  detectedAt        DateTime @default(now())
  confidence        Float    @default(0.7)   // stored internally — NEVER shown as a %
  reason            String?                   // AI reasoning or rule note
  source            String   @default("ai")   // "ai" | "rule"
  @@unique([upstreamIssueId, downstreamIssueId])
}
```

Issue also carries: `chainRootIssueId String?`, `upstreamLinks IssueChainLink[]`,
`downstreamLinks IssueChainLink[]`.

## UI

- **Authority dashboard** shows a "Cascading Complaints" panel (HEAD only) — alerts grouped
  by chain root, each linking to the root issue.
- **Issue detail** (authority + citizen) shows a soft amber `CascadeLinkBanner` —
  "May be caused by: [upstream]" — with a provenance badge ("AI-detected" / "Auto-linked"),
  the reason sentence, and a **qualitative strength band** (Strong / Likely / Possible),
  **never a %**. The HEAD additionally sees a "Not related" undo control; citizens/employees
  see the provenance but cannot undo.
- When an upstream issue is RESOLVED and still has open downstream issues, the HEAD is
  offered a **Cascade Resolve** card (`cascade-resolve-card.tsx`) to batch-mark downstream
  issues resolved, with a provenance note. Resolved downstream issues remain
  community-disputable (REOPENED path).

## Coexistence with RootIssue

Chain links are separate from the flat RootIssue grouping — both can coexist. Chains are
directed (cause → effect); RootIssues are flat groupings of symptoms under one systemic title.

