# Attention Rules (Age-Based — NOT SLA-Based)

Computed on page load. No background jobs.

**There are no SLAs and no priority multipliers.** These are factual "needs attention" flags
based on how long an issue has sat in its current status. They never claim a deadline was
missed or promise a fix date.

Attention thresholds (plain days, no multiplier):

| Status | Threshold | Who owns this wait |
|--------|-----------|-------------------|
| SUBMITTED | > 3 days | Community / HEAD (unverified too long) |
| VERIFIED | > 3 days | Section head / HEAD (sat unassigned) |
| ASSIGNED / IN_PROGRESS / REOPENED | > 14 days | Assigned officer |

When an issue crosses its threshold:
- The `AttentionBadge` turns amber; at 2× threshold it turns red.
- A reason label is shown ("Unverified 5d", "Unassigned 3d", "Open 17d").
- The dashboard "Needs Attention" section surfaces it and sorts by days-in-status.

**Commitment date** (stored as `dueDate`): a voluntary promise by the LOCAL_BODY_HEAD or
section head. If the date has passed, the badge shows "Commitment Nd ago" — a factual record
of a real human commitment, separate from the attention threshold.

**Phase timestamps** (on Issue): `verifiedAt`, `assignedAt`, `resolvedAt` — used for
phase-split performance analytics on the Team page.

Do NOT reintroduce `SLA_HOURS`, `PRIORITY_MULTIPLIERS`, `computeEscalation`, or
`impactConfidencePct`. Those have been deleted. Use `needsAttention()` from `src/lib/utils.ts`.

# Authority Dashboard — Map-First Interface (STORY-011)

The authority dashboard (`/authority/dashboard`) is a **full-viewport map-first workspace**,
not a card-based page. The map fills the entire screen below the nav; all content floats on
top of it — Google Maps / Uber style.

## Layout structure

- **`AuthorityIssueMap`** (`src/components/civic/authority-issue-map.tsx`) is the root
  component. It renders a full-viewport Mapbox map (`h-[calc(100vh-3.5rem)]`) with:
  - A **floating left panel** (Google-Maps-style): header + jurisdiction, stat chips, status
    filter chips, role insight panels passed as `children`, and a scrollable results list.
  - A **bottom-right detail card** when a marker or list row is selected (title, badges,
    community impact, attention badge, Open / Assign actions).
  - A **priority legend** at the bottom center.
  - Marker click or list-row click → `flyTo` the location + open detail card.
- **Authority layout** (`src/app/authority/layout.tsx`) is full-bleed (`flex-1` only, no
  `max-w` or padding) so the dashboard can occupy the full viewport. Other authority pages
  (`/authority/team`, `/authority/issues/[id]`) carry their own `mx-auto max-w-* px-4 py-6`
  centered wrapper.

## Map content

- Markers = role-scoped issue set (HEAD → all municipality issues; EMPLOYEE/section head →
  their assigned issues). Coloured by priority, sized by community impact.
- Status filter chips in the left panel filter markers client-side.
- Insight panels (root cause, cascading, verification queue, section queue, needs-attention)
  are rendered inside the left panel via the `children` prop — they live in the **server
  component** dashboard page, so data fetching and RBAC stay server-side.

## When no Mapbox token

The full-viewport area shows a "set token" message. The left panel and all insight panels
remain fully functional.

