`LOCAL_BODY_HEAD` is the **municipal executive**, managing all staff across the municipality.
Staff are organised into **sections (शाखा)**. Use the `Department` enum (in `@/generated/prisma/client`):

| `Department` | Palika Section | Category values it owns |
|---|---|---|
| `TECHNICAL_INFRASTRUCTURE` | Prabidhik / Engineering | ROAD, INFRASTRUCTURE |
| `WATER_SANITATION` | Khanepani tatha Sarsafai | WATER_SANITATION |
| `ENVIRONMENT_WASTE` | Fohor / Watawaran | WASTE_MANAGEMENT, ENVIRONMENT |
| `ELECTRICITY_LIGHTING` | Batti / Street lighting | ELECTRICITY |
| `DISASTER_PUBLIC_SAFETY` | Vipad / Suraksha | PUBLIC_SAFETY |
| `ADMINISTRATION` | Prashasan / General | OTHER |

Use `categoryToDepartment(category)` from `src/lib/departments.ts` for the mapping.

Each employee has `department`, `wardNumber` (deployment ward), `isActive`, `isSectionHead` fields.
One section head per section. Promoting one demotes the previous.

**Assignment is two-tier.** The section head receives VERIFIED issues for their section and
assigns to officers within it. The HEAD assigns directly as an override. Neither auto-assigns.
Enforce this in `assignIssueAction` — section heads can only assign issues in their section
to officers in their section.

---

AI may:

* Categorize reports (category enum)
* Suggest priority (LOW / MEDIUM / HIGH / CRITICAL)
* Detect semantic duplicates (similarity score + matched issueId) — only after geospatial check finds no match
* Suggest root causes (title + reason + confidence + related issue IDs)
* Detect cascading causal links (upstream cause for a new issue + reasoning) — see "Cascading Issue Chains"; stored as an `IssueChainLink`, reversible by the HEAD
* Auto-elevate priority to HIGH when reportCount ≥ 8, CRITICAL when ≥ 15 (arithmetic on a count — the one exception to the human-approval rule)

AI must NEVER:

* Automatically resolve issues
* Automatically assign responsibility
* Automatically escalate issues
* Create any database record directly
* Output a "% confidence" number for display — AI confidence is either stored internally (for threshold checks like 0.65) or shown as a qualitative band in UI

Human validation is always required for all AI suggestions.

All AI calls use Gemini with structured JSON output. Parse and validate before storing.

